cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper deals with pedestrian tracking in crowd scenes using a new high-definition crowd video dataset. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics): The use of velocity-obstacles and multi-agent motion model can be relevant to robotics applications such as autonomous navigation of robots in crowded environments. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper considers local interactions between pedestrians and takes into account personal constraints, which can be relevant to social network analysis. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper uses a new high-definition crowd video dataset to evaluate the performance of different pedestrian tracking algorithms. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses an adaptive particle filtering scheme that dynamically changes the number of particles allocated to each pedestrian based on different confidence metrics, which can be relevant to machine learning.
